# Outside Inn Radio — Complete Launch Record
**From 480 PNGs to 24/7 Live Stream**
*Built: March 2, 2026 | Last updated: March 3, 2026*

---

## Purpose of This Document

This is the definitive technical record of how the Outside Inn 24/7 lo-fi radio stream was built, launched, and operated through its first night. It serves two purposes: (1) a reference for explaining the launch to others, and (2) a context document for AI-assisted troubleshooting and future rebuilds. Every file, command, decision, pivot, and problem encountered is recorded here.

---

## How the Whole Thing Works — Master Architecture

### The two modes

**Mode 1 — Lo-Fi Radio (default, 24/7)**
A cloud server (DigitalOcean VPS) in New York runs a video file on repeat, forever, and pushes it to Restream, which forwards it to YouTube. Evan's laptop can be off, closed, or in another country. The server costs $6/month and runs independently of everything else.

**Mode 2 — Live Stream (when Evan goes live)**
Evan's laptop runs OBS, which pushes the live stream to Restream, which forwards it to YouTube. During this time, the VPS is paused. YouTube sees one continuous stream source at a time — you can't have both running simultaneously or they'll conflict.

### The handoff
Switching between modes always causes a brief blip on YouTube (a few seconds of reconnecting). This is unavoidable — YouTube doesn't allow two encoders at once. The goal is to make it fast, not eliminate it entirely.

### The players

| What | What it does | Where |
|---|---|---|
| DigitalOcean VPS | Cloud server that runs Holdt 24/7 | digitalocean.com — IP: 138.197.9.139 |
| FFmpeg | Software on the server that loops the video and pushes it | Runs inside the server |
| tmux | Keeps FFmpeg running even when the terminal is closed | Session named "stream" on the server |
| HoldtLoop.mp4 | The video file — 1h40m, Holdt animation + lo-fi music | /root/HoldtLoop.mp4 on the server |
| Restream | Receives video from VPS or OBS and forwards to YouTube | restream.io — innkeep@outsideinn.tv |
| OBS | Evan's streaming software on the laptop | GIGABYTE AERO X16 |
| YouTube | Where viewers watch | Channel: @EIWerner |

