## Phase 5 — Cloud Infrastructure Setup (DigitalOcean VPS)

Why a VPS instead of streaming from the laptop: Restream's native scheduler maxes out at 10 loops (~40 hours) and requires manual rescheduling. A VPS running FFmpeg loops infinitely for $6/month with no intervention.

16. Created DigitalOcean account (innkeep@outsideinn.tv), added company card, received $200 free credit (60-day expiry)
17. Spun up a droplet with these specs:
   - Image: Ubuntu 24.04 LTS
   - Size: $6/mo — 1GB RAM, 1 vCPU, 25GB SSD, 1TB transfer
   - Region: NYC3 (New York)
   - Auth: Password
   - IP: 138.197.9.139
   - Hostname: ubuntu-s-1vcpu-1gb-nyc3-01
   - Note: 512MB RAM droplet was considered but rejected — too tight for FFmpeg under load
18. SSH'd into the server from Windows PowerShell: ssh root@138.197.9.139
19. Installed FFmpeg: apt install ffmpeg -y (194 packages, ~595MB)

---

## Phase 6 — Restream Setup

Architecture: VPS FFmpeg → Restream RTMP ingest → Restream routes to YouTube (and Twitch when added).

20. Logged into Restream account (innkeep@outsideinn.tv)
21. Located RTMP credentials under Channel/Settings:
   - RTMP URL: rtmp://live.restream.io/live/
   - Stream key: re_10860387_75ea120b5509c4a2572f
22. Upgraded from Free to Standard plan ($16/mo billed annually, ~$192/year) to remove Restream branding watermark. Standard supports 3 channels — sufficient for YouTube + Twitch + one more.
   - Free plan was rejected: it overlays a Restream branding watermark visible to all viewers
   - Professional ($39/mo) and Business ($199/mo) plans not needed at this stage

