## Phase 7 — Uploading the File to VPS

Common mistake to avoid: Running scp from inside the SSH session tries to find the file on the server, not the laptop. Must be run from a local terminal window. This mistake was made once during the build.

23. Opened a fresh PowerShell window (separate from the active SSH session)
24. Uploaded HoldtLoop.mp4 from laptop SSD to VPS:

```
scp D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtLoop.mp4 root@138.197.9.139:/root/
```

25. Upload completed: 1.28GB at ~3.3MB/s, ~6 minutes 37 seconds
26. File now lives at /root/HoldtLoop.mp4 on the VPS

---

## Phase 8 — Starting the 24/7 Stream

Why tmux: If you close the SSH window without tmux, the FFmpeg process dies and the stream stops. tmux keeps the process running in a persistent session on the server.

27. SSH'd back into the VPS: ssh root@138.197.9.139
28. Installed tmux: apt install tmux -y
29. Created a persistent named session: tmux new -s stream
30. Inside the tmux session, launched FFmpeg to stream continuously to Restream:

```
ffmpeg -re -stream_loop -1 -i HoldtLoop.mp4 -c:v copy -c:a copy -f flv rtmp://live.restream.io/live/re_10860387_75ea120b5509c4a2572f
```

Command breakdown:
- -re — reads input at native frame rate (real-time, not as fast as possible)
- -stream_loop -1 — loops the file infinitely
- -c:v copy -c:a copy — stream copies without re-encoding (no quality loss, minimal CPU)
- -f flv — FLV container format required for RTMP streaming

31. Confirmed stream running:
   - Health: EXCELLENT
   - Resolution: 1920x1080
   - Bitrate: ~1820 Kbps
   - Frame rate: 6fps
   - time=00:00:27.05, speed=1.02x

To detach from tmux without stopping the stream: Press Ctrl+B, release fully, then D
To reattach later: tmux attach -t stream
To stop the stream: Reattach, then press Q

---

## Phase 9 — Connecting to YouTube

How Restream → YouTube works: Restream connects via OAuth (Google account authorization), not stream keys. It creates its own stream on your YouTube channel automatically. YouTube Studio's default "Default stream key" page will show "No data" — this confused troubleshooting for ~30 minutes. You must navigate to the stream Restream created.

32. In Restream dashboard, clicked Add Channel → selected YouTube → authorized via Google OAuth
33. Toggled YouTube channel ON — Restream confirmed "Sending data..."
34. In YouTube Studio, yellow error bar appeared: "Stream key is currently assigned. Select a new key or change it in inspired lofi to write with // ad-free [Alpha]" — this is expected. Clicked "Change dashboard" to navigate to the correct stream.
35. Stream title: "inspired lofi to write with // ad-free [Alpha]"
36. Category changed from Gaming → People & Blogs
37. Privacy: Public
38. Thumbnail: selected a still PNG from Marwan's frames, compressed from ~233KB PNG to under 2MB JPEG using squoosh.app at 80% JPEG quality, uploaded to YouTube
39. Confirmed live on YouTube → red LIVE badge visible

Note on YouTube stream management: Restream creates new stream entries each session. Over time this creates multiple entries in YouTube Studio. The active one is always the one showing the red LIVE badge. Old entries can be deleted from YouTube Studio → Content → Live.

